 I just wanted to introduce myself and see what kind of list and how active 
this list is. My name is Alex Vieira and I've been involved with VWs since I 
was a teenager. I live in Colorado Springs, CO, and am a charter member of 
the Colorado VW Bus Club. I have a '63 Standard and a '65 Kombi (people 
hauler and crap hauler, respectively) and I am currently building my first 
engine for the '63 (it's nerve-wracking the first time!). I'm getting back 
into the scene after taking a couple of years off to get out of debt, buy a 
house, etc., but I'm looking forward to participating in some club and local 
events here in CO. I'm also into aircooled BMW twins (affectionately called 
'airheads' by those in-the-know), and belong to a couple of clubs through 
that interest as well.
 
